text: Arizona's 15th Legislative District is one of 30 in the state, situated entirely in Maricopa County. As of 2018 there are 42 precincts in the district, with a total registered voter population of 142,352. ==Political representation== The district is represented for the 2019-2021 Legislative Session in the State Senate by Heather Carter (R, Cave Creek) and in the House of Representatives by Nancy Barto (R, Phoenix) and John Allen (R, Scottsdale). ==References== Category:Maricopa County, Arizona Category:Arizona legislative districts
title: Arizona's 15th legislative district
